Due to the pandemic in Europe, many countries in the Schengen Area restrict free movement and create border controls.
The national response included containment measures, such as quarantine (known as a stay-at-home order, a place-of-shelter order, or provincial quarantine) and nighttime. On April 2, nearly 300 million people, or about 90% of the population, were in some form of provincial quarantine in the United States, more than 50 million people were in provincial quarantine in the Philippines, about 59 million people were in provincial quarantine in South Africa, and 1.3 billion people were in provincial quarantine in India.
