This medication may not be safe for use by pregnant women or people trying to conceive.
A study of lopinavir/ritonavir (Kaletra), a combination of the lopinavir and ritonavir antiviruses, concluded that there were no observed benefits.
The drug is designed to inhibit HIV replication by binding protease.
